{
  "destination": {
    "name": "Úbeda",
    "description": "Important and populous city located on the hills of its namesake, in the geographical center of the province, in a landscape populated by olive trees and cereal fields.\n\nÚbeda is an artistic and monumental city, no matter where you look, and one of the most stately and glorious towns in Andalusia. Castilian and Renaissance on all sides, it contains such a quantity of monuments, churches, palaces, and stately homes that the best thing to do is to stroll through it and virtually transport oneself to the time of its historical splendor: The Chapel of El Salvador, located in the incomparable square of the Town Hall, the Church of S. Pablo, the Church of Santa María de los Reales Alcázares, the Church of La Trinidad, the Oratory of San Juan de la Cruz, Monastery of Santa Clara, Vela de los Cobos Palace, Las Cadenas Palace, Casa de las Torres, Santiago Hospital, Hospital of the Honored Old of El Salvador, Clock Tower, Walls of La Cava, Pottery Museum, and the National Parador of Tourism, are some of the wonders that this surprising city contains.\n\nIn addition to these attractions, a visit to the walls and the splendid view obtained from there is suggested, as well as to its potters, especially to the house-museum of Paco Titos.",
